body.name: Pampers Baby Dry Diapers - Size 3, 168 Count, Absorbent Disposable Diapers
features: Up to 100% leakproof nights and happy mornings with LockAway Channels
Helps prevent leaks with stretchy sides and large tape fasteners for a secure and comfortable fit
Helps keep skin dry and healthy with Dri-Weave Liner
Trusted protection—from Pampers #1 pediatrician recommended brand* (*Based on a 2021 survey of U.S. and Canadian pediatricians)
Gentle on baby’s delicate skin—hypoallergenic and free of parabens and latex* (*Natural Rubber)
Use with Pampers Baby-Clean wipes to keep baby's skin clean and dry
body.description: A good night’s sleep starts with a great diaper, and Pampers Baby-Dry diapers give you and your baby up to 100% leakproof nights and happy mornings. Made to protect your baby’s delicate skin, our exclusive LockAway Channels absorb wetness and lock it safely away, while our protective Dri-Weave Liner helps keep skin healthy. Plus, our Baby-Dry Diapers are hypoallergenic and completely free of parabens and latex.* These are just a few of the many reasons Pampers is the #1 pediatrician recommended diaper brand—and your baby's best bet for comfy protection. Pampers also keep messes to a minimum. To help contain leaks and prevent blowouts, our Baby-Dry diapers feature all-around stretchy sides and large tape fasteners for a secure and comfy fit. Plus, they come equipped with our Dual Leak-Guard Barriers that are specially designed to protect around the legs, where leaks tend to happen most. And when your baby is due for a diaper change, our handy Wetness Indicator lets you know. No need for guesswork. Use Baby-Dry diapers with our Pampers Sensitive Wipes to help keep your baby’s skin healthy and prevent irritation. New & improved! Packaging and prints may vary. Ships in 100% recyclable packaging. *Natural Rubber

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Find the Right Fit Babies come in all shapes and sizes—follow these steps for a comfortable and secure fit Front Fit The diaper should fit just under your baby’s belly button Leg Cuff Fit After the diaper is on, run two fingers just inside the leg cuffs so there is no gapping or bunching Waist & Fastening When fastened, you should just about be able to run two fingers around the waist Signs of a Good Fit No leaks and no red marks when you remove the diaper

How do Pampers Baby-Dry help prevent leaks? Pampers Baby-Dry features 3 layers of absorbency to pull liquid away and all-around stretchy sides for a secure, comfortable fit. Can my baby wear Baby-Dry day or night? Yes! Baby-Dry has 3 Extra Absorb Channels that help distribute wetness evenly and lock it away for up to 12 hours. Are Pampers Baby-Dry ingredients safe for my little one’s skin? Yes! All materials in Pampers diapers are carefully selected and thoroughly evaluated for safety and skin compatibility. Pampers is the #1 Pediatrician Recommended Brand and is free of parabens and latex. What do you mean “packaging may vary”? We've recently made aesthetic changes. You may receive either package and product during this time. Rest assured your product is genuine and made by Pampers, but if you have questions please reach out to us directly. Does Pampers Baby-Dry have a Wetness Indicator? Yes! On sizes N, 1, and 2, the Wetness Indicator helps you know when your baby may be ready for a change.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2011
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So far so good!
reviews.reviewText: I used these for my little boy last night and they held up! Of course this is only the first night that he's used them but already I'm impressed. My stash of Fisher Price diapers which by the way I HATE! They leaked almost every night but this review is not for them...so...back to my Pampers! The fit is nice the design is cute and best of all they have not leaked! I'm happy so far and will be back in about a week or so for an update! If you're interested in my review the fisher price diapers check out my profile and reviews!Update! One week into my package of Pampers baby dry and wow...all I can say is wow! No leaks at all! I've used brands like Huggies Supreme, Huggies Over nights, Diapers.com, Fisher Price <---Sucks! Out of all the brands I've used these are the best! I've had no leaks at all! These hold it all in even better than the Huggies Overnights which were made for well...Over nights! I have a new favorite brand and I'm so happy I tried these! I would recommend these diapers to parents who are looking for excellent leak protection!Update #2 This is my last and final update...Almost three weeks into the box of diapers and I'm still happy as ever! My husband even took notice! He recently said..."we haven't had any leaks have we?" I proudly said "Nope, not one!" I know I said this before but these are way better than even the Huggies Overnights! I love these and will be sticking with Pampers from here on out!Unfortunately I have to give another update: Although I have had no leaks at all, toward the end of the box my son started to develop this nasty rash. I recently bought a box of Pampers Swaddlers, so we will see how that goes. So far I'm not thrilled with Pampers. :( It's great that there have been no leaks, but my son has a nasty rash! What is that about?!?

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 23, 2016
reviews.reviewText: Pampers Baby Dry is the only diaper that would remain leak-free throughout the night when both my baby girls began sleeping through the night. We generally use Swaddlers or Cruisers at our house but we have on occasion used the Pampers Dry Baby. They seem to work just as well as any of the other versions of pampers that we have used. This diaper is absolutely worth every penny! It kept my babies dry and comfortable and saved me time, money, and energy from not having to change and wash crib sheets every morning. This is a must have for babies that are sleeping long stretches through the night! These are AMAZING! I love the elastic tabs, they move and adjust with the baby unlike other brands that don't have elastic tabs which cause an uncomfortable fit/adjustment. I will never buy another brand. These diapers can absorb liquid like nothing I've ever seen and are just all around great quality!We have no complaints with Pampers products and we would recommend them to any one!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 31, 2013
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great diapers!! No leaking and fit well
reviews.reviewText: As we all know, diapers and babies are very individual. What works for one, doesn't work for another. I started out using Pampers swaddlers, and loved them. I tried Huggies Naturals and they leaked horribly. My daughter isn't a huge pee-er and those diapers would leak out the top in the front constantly. Luvs gave her a horrible rash on her tummy and back from the first time I used one. So I went back to the Pampers. I decided to try the baby dry since I hate to change her diaper in the night and wake her up. So far so good. Haven't had any leaks, no diaper rash, and seems to keep her skin pretty dry even after 12 plus hours over night. The diapers are thin, but that doesn't effect their function. They hold ALOT of liquid. I actually like the thinness. Makes her pants less bulky and easier to snap a onsie on. I'm a Pampers girl from now on. So far the best diapers I've tried. They may cost a bit more, but with diapers, I'm finding out you get what you pay for. There's nothing I don't like about these.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars No more blowouts!
reviews.reviewText: These are such a great value! My go to overnight diapers. My baby is 4 mo old as of this review and totally breastfed, so she pees a lot! This is the only diaper that even comes close to absorbing it all without leaking. I had some leftover target brand from my last baby that I put her in during the day, just to use them up, but she immediately got a rash, and has a blowout EVERY time she poops. These didn't leak even after wearing it all night then pooping in the morning. I might just have to give away the whole box of target brand. Some days she poops 4x a day, which means 4 dirty outfits per day. The cost of these with a subscription is actually cheaper than the generic brand. Premium diapers at a generic price! I've been telling everyone. This is cheaper than cloth diapering. I can't pay for water and soap, never mind my time for as cheap as these are, about .12-.15 per diaper depending on the size and even better if you find an amazon coupon.Update: picture is 11 hours overnight in the same diaper. It absorbed everything and she and her outfit are dry and rash free. Yay, for no more midnight diaper changes!

reviews.reviewTitle: Good diapers, never have had a diaper leak in the night and baby has had no bad reactions on her skin
reviews.reviewText: All we use for our baby and she loves them. We've used these for the past 3-4 months now from when our baby was around 5-6 months old and size 1 was getting tighter around her belly. I think we're just getting to the size 3 diapers now at 9 months.They fit well, hold lots of liquid so we have never had any accidents during the night. Very impressed, and the grandparents can't believe how far diapers have come! They complained about having all sorts of accidents back when they had us, and now diaper "technology" has come so far that we can buy inexpensive diapers by the hundreds and not have to worry about daily or nightly leaks!Also I should mention that our baby didn't have any bad reactions to the diapers. We use baby lotion a few times a week and baby power usually after every diaper change.

I love these diapers... from early on, our son was a big eater (read: big pee's and poops) and sleeping through the night for 9 - 12 hours. These diapers have never let us down in 6 months... ie no leaks, no wetness on his body, even with huge "super soakers" after a long night's sleep. Great price (especially on amazon) and who wouldn't want the big boxes delivered to your doorstep rather than schlepping them home from a store!
